          <m>\surfaceS</m>is the paraboloid
          <m>z=x^2+y^2</m> over the triangle with vertices at <m>(0,0)</m>,
          <m>(0,1)</m> and <m>(1,1)</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>S = \int_0^1\int_0^1\sqrt{v^2+4u^2v^2+4v^4}\, du\, dv \approx 0.931</m>.
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>\surfaceS</m>is the plane <m>z=5x-y</m> over the region enclosed by the parabola <m>y=1-x^2</m> and the <m>x</m>-axis.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>S =\int_0^1\int_{-1}^{1}\sqrt{(5u^2-2uv-5)^2+u^4+(1-u^2)^2}\, du\, dv \approx 7.084</m>.
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>\surfaceS</m>is the hyperbolic paraboloid
          <m>z=x^2-y^2</m> over the circular disk of radius 1 centered at the origin.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>S =\int_0^1\int_{0}^{2\pi}\sqrt{v^2+4v^4}\, du\, dv = (5\sqrt{5}-1)\pi/6 \approx 5.330</m>.
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
  </subsection>

